features.name: Historic Old Town Scottsdale
features.summary: Scottsdale began as a small farming community when a banker from Rhode Island subdivided 40 acres of desert land into town lots in 1894. He named it after Winfield Scott, who was responsible for getting most of the early settlers to the new community.
